## Admin Panel CSS Style Guide

When writing or modifying styles in `src/app/(payload)/styles/`:

1. **Component-First Approach**:
   - Each component gets its own file in `components/` directory
   - Import the file in `admin.scss`
   - Keep related styles together

2. **Use Design Tokens**:
   ```scss
   // ✅ Good - uses variables
   color: $admin-text-primary;
   padding: $spacing-lg;
   
   // ❌ Bad - hard-coded values
   color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.9);
   padding: 1rem;
   ```

3. **Use Mixins for Patterns**:
   ```scss
   // ✅ Good - reusable mixin
   .my-card {
     @include gradient-border;
     @include card-hover;
   }
   
   // ❌ Bad - repeating complex pattern
   .my-card {
     border: 2px solid transparent;
     position: relative;
     &::before { /* 15 lines of gradient border code */ }
   }
   ```

4. **Naming Conventions**:
   - Use descriptive class names (`.nav__link`, not `.nl`)
   - Use BEM-style for components (`.block__element--modifier`)
   - Prefix admin-specific classes if needed

5. **Nesting Depth**:
   ```scss
   // ✅ Good - max 3 levels
   .card {
     .card__header {
       .card__title { }
     }
   }
   
   // ❌ Bad - too deep
   .container .section .card .header .title .text { }
   ```

6. **Comments**:
   - Add section headers for groups of related styles
   - Explain WHY, not WHAT (code shows what)
   - Document any non-obvious patterns or workarounds
